<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,310,1433,1459]" box="[189,310,1433,1459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1433,1459]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1433,1459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[186,1399,1479,1611]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
Species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buckton" authorityYear="1905" box="[540,633,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[540,633,1480,1505]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Hamma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the thorax entirely black and pronotum smooth; suprahumeral horns with a laterally pointing thorn; a posterior process with four nodes, V-shaped in lateral view between the second and fourth nodes; last node roundish in dorsal view, ending in a well-developed terminal spine. Pterostigma about three times as long as broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,457,1650,1676]" box="[189,457,1650,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,1650,1676]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,1650,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[187,1399,1697,1794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
The general black colour clearly distinguishes this species from the following two (i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1207,1302,1697,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1207,1302,1697,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1399,1697,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[237,349,1733,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[237,349,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[354,446,1733,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), although not from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulard" authorityYear="1968" box="[675,838,1732,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heimi">
<emphasis box="[675,838,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Hamma heimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The roughly triangular shape of the supraocular callosity (
<figureCitation box="[302,393,1767,1793]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) is also diagnostic with respect to all other species in the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1398,1833,1930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">
The anchor-like third node (
<figureCitation box="[534,627,1833,1860]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[252,1342,283,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[239,1348,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 5. Morphology. Pterostigma of right wing in dorsal view; third node of the posterior process in dorsal view; scutellum in lateral right view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745167/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) of the posterior process clearly distinguishes it from all other species in the group, being rhomboidal in dorsal view, whereas it is roughly circular in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulard" authorityYear="1968" box="[1213,1278,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heimi">
<emphasis box="[1213,1278,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">heimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and truly anchor-like in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[359,454,1903,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[359,454,1903,1929]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[461,552,1904,1930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[639,751,1904,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[639,751,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="94">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[758,849,1904,1930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="94" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1259,265,292]" box="[189,1259,265,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
Other diagnostic characters with respect to 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[697,792,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[697,792,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[799,890,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[946,1058,266,291]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[946,1058,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1066,1157,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
include:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,315,553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
– upper margin of the head (
<figureCitation box="[530,619,315,341]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) roughly circular (roughly square in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1041,1136,315,341]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1041,1136,315,341]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1143,1232,316,342]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1284,1396,316,341]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1284,1396,316,341]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[227,321,351,377]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,315,553]" box="[189,1239,386,412]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
– metopidium (
<figureCitation box="[385,475,386,412]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) smooth (tuberculate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[762,857,386,412]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[762,857,386,412]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[864,955,386,412]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1011,1123,386,411]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1011,1123,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1131,1225,386,412]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,315,553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
– suprahumeral horns (
<figureCitation box="[473,563,421,447]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) with a robust thorn slightly curving dorsally in frontal view (straight in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[226,321,456,482]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[226,321,456,482]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[329,419,457,483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[476,588,457,482]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[476,588,457,482]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,690,457,483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,315,553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
– pterostigma (
